 learn how to store data with meaningful labels instead of just positions: looking values up by name with dictionaries, nesting them when each entry has its own details, and bundling related values that shouldn't change into tuples. We'll also learn to choose when a labelled lookup is the right shape and when a plain list is enough. We'll put those ideas together into a simple Food Delivery Order Tracker that displays a menu, builds a cart from the user's picks, and prints a clean order summary with the total.